=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-pdf\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-pdf\"></use></svg>Download PDF</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportTopicButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"singlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportSubtopicsButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"pdfWithChildren\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic and subtopics</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportBundleButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"wholeBundlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save entire publication</a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicShare zDocsShareButton\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Share\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex zDocsShareDialogButton\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Share\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none zDocsShareDialogButton\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg>Share</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareEmail\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Email Link</span></a><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareLink\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Copy Link</span></a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsFeedback zDocsFeedback zDocsTopicFeedback\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-label=\"Feedback\" class=\"zDocsFeedbackButton d-none d-lg-flex\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2534145\" data-toggle=\"modal\" data-tooltip-content=\"Feedback\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2534145\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Sept 04, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104ylz1665702772622.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/ylz1665702772622.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/ylz1665702772622.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"ylz1665702772622\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Call Stored Procedure Components\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"ylz1665702772622__call_stored_procedure_components_117079\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">To call a stored procedure component, use the ProcScript <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">activate</span> statement.\n </p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ylz1665702772622__li_d18596e1_d18597e1_d18598e1\">Use the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">activate</span> statement to invoke the stored procedure as follows:\n <p class=\"p\" id=\"ylz1665702772622__p_d36380e1_d36381e1_d36382e1\">\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">activate</span>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">InstanceName</var>.<var class=\"keyword varname\">OperationName</var> (<var class=\"keyword varname\">Parameter1</var>,...<var class=\"keyword varname\">ParameterN</var>)</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ylz1665702772622__li_d18599e1_d18600e1_d18601e1\">\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">InstanceName</var> is the name of the component instance. This has a maximum length of 16 bytes for Uniface components, or 32 bytes for non-Uniface components.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ylz1665702772622__li_d18602e1_d18603e1_d18604e1\">\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">OperationName</var> is the required operation of the stored procedure component. This is mapped to a stored procedure name. Therefore, the operation name must resemble the stored procedure name.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ylz1665702772622__li_d18605e1_d18606e1_d18607e1\">\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">Parameter1</var> through <var class=\"keyword varname\">ParameterN</var> are the operation’s parameters. The number and order of the parameters you specify must match those within the stored procedure. The operation parameter name is mapped to a formal parameter name within the stored procedure. Therefore, all operation parameter names must resemble the stored procedure parameter names.\n </li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ylz1665702772622__p_d36383e1_d36384e1_d36385e1\">For information on DBMS-specific requirements or restrictions, see the relevant connector information.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<div class=\"example\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ylz1665702772622__p_d36386e1_d36387e1_d36388e1\">The service stored procedure, ENDOFMONTH, has two basic parameters. The first is an input string parameter specifying the month, and the second is an output numeric parameter specifying a derived monthly total.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ylz1665702772622__p_d36389e1_d36390e1_d36391e1\">The ENDOFMONTH component is located on a remote machine, MyHOST. The client assignment file contains the following:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">$STORED_PROCS tcp:MyHost|User|Password| + SRU:|||\nENDOFMONTH = $STORED_PROCS:ENDOFMONTH</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ylz1665702772622__p_d36392e1_d36393e1_d36394e1\">The stored procedure is activated as follows:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">activate \"ENDOFMONTH\".ENDOFMONTH ($in$, $out$)</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/fxx1665702529732.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>activate</a><p>Calls an operation on a component instance.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/yqa1665702772542.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Naming Specifications for Service Store Procedures</a><p>For Service Stored Procedures, the signature of the Stored Procedure Component maps the names of Uniface components, operations, and parameters to the name of a package, procedure, and parameter names in the procedure.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ffw1719409087502.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>SQL and Stored Procedures Support</a><p>For SQL-enabled databases, you can use the sql ProcScript instruction and SQL Editor to send SQL instructions to the database. Some databases also support stored procedures.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2534145\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2534145\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Call Stored Procedure Components Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Sept 04, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Call Stored Procedure Components To call a stored procedure component, use the ProcScript activate statement. Use the activate statement to invoke the stored procedure as follows: activate InstanceName . OperationName ( Parameter1 ,... ParameterN ) InstanceName is the name of the component instance. This has a maximum length of 16 bytes for Uniface components, or 32 bytes for non-Uniface components. OperationName is the required operation of the stored procedure component. This is mapped to a stored procedure name. Therefore, the operation name must resemble the stored procedure name. Parameter1 through ParameterN are the operation’s parameters. The number and order of the parameters you specify must match those within the stored procedure. The operation parameter name is mapped to a formal parameter name within the stored procedure. Therefore, all operation parameter names must resemble the stored procedure parameter names. For information on DBMS-specific requirements or restrictions, see the relevant connector information. The service stored procedure, ENDOFMONTH, has two basic parameters. The first is an input string parameter specifying the month, and the second is an output numeric parameter specifying a derived monthly total. The ENDOFMONTH component is located on a remote machine, MyHOST. The client assignment file contains the following: $STORED_PROCS tcp:MyHost|User|Password| + SRU:||| ENDOFMONTH = $STORED_PROCS:ENDOFMONTH Copy The stored procedure is activated as follows: activate \"ENDOFMONTH\".ENDOFMONTH ($in$, $out$) Copy Related Links activate Calls an operation on a component instance. Naming Specifications for Service Store Procedures For Service Stored Procedures, the signature of the Stored Procedure Component maps the names of Uniface components, operations, and parameters to the name of a package, procedure, and parameter names in the procedure. SQL and Stored Procedures Support For SQL-enabled databases, you can use the sql ProcScript instruction and SQL Editor to send SQL instructions to the database. Some databases also support stored procedures. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}